{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6610", "repo": "rails", "body": "@drogus - I think we should focus on usecases when people execute commands intentionally, properly and with knowledge about what they are doing. I also think that they can easily test the changes and revert in case they don not like the result of their accidental command execution. Please remember that the required version of gems are hardcoded in `Gemfile.lock`. `Gemfile` is about how I want to be able to upgrade my application in future. Which gem versions I believe could cooperate together.", "_id": {"$oid": "52380636bd3543c15100c8a9"}, "issue_id": 6610, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6127844", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6610#issuecomment-6127844", "updated_at": "2012-06-05T15:27:35Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq", "login": "paneq", "gravatar_id": "9b81cae1fb43808ac23a2188258ca9e4", "html_url": "https://github.com/paneq", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/9b81cae1fb43808ac23a2188258ca9e4?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F180bb054f1a36e1777b05a0664a7eb71.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 65587, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-06-05T15:27:35Z", "id": 6127844, "owner": "rails"}
